MAFDET (Port Mafdet) — fortified beach city at eastern terminus of Saltglass
Reach, where inland desert corridor meets the sea. Named for guardian Mafdet:
feline divine executioner of thieves, oath-breakers, and those who prey on the
defenseless. Legitimacy = reliable docking, fair weights, enforceable manifests.
It is a transaction city.

STRANDLINE COMPACT (three blocs; any two can veto the third):
Harbor first: no political decision may obstruct port operations
Dual attestation: all cargo verified under both inland and maritime standards
Swift judgment: commercial disputes resolved within three tides

HARBOR WARDENS: Quay security, anti-piracy, harbor chain (raised every night
since the Fracture Era — never failed). Warden-Commander's Harbor Register:
100+ years of records. Authority ends at the shore.

LEDGER HOUSES:
Tide Ledger Hall: bulk commodities; Saltweight weights recalibrated annually
Shoreward House: bilingual clerks, oasis/maritime legal notation
Storm Ledger: insurance, escrow, storm advisories
Quarantine Ledger: relic/hazardous pyramid cargo; smallest, most sensitive;
recent seizures under sealed review

SHRINE OF THE FIRST CLAW: Trade oaths sealed on basalt feline forepaw (worn
smooth); recorded on wax-and-bitumen tablets. Breaking oath = permanent trade
exclusion. Claw Mark Registry tracks all oaths and penalties across years.
Swift Court: three-tide judgment, final, no appeal except for inter-city
treaty matters.

SAND-SEA CARTERS' GUILD: Controls all Saltglass Reach transit and pyramid
corridor linkage. Contracts non-negotiable. Without the Guild, the harbor has
nothing to load.

CURRENT FACTIONS:
Quay Concord: senior captains/Wardens; maritime reliability above politics
Red Sand Accounts: inland debts → maritime obligations → Mafdet courts;
technically legal; widely despised
Jackal Synod: smuggles pyramid ritual components under false manifests
Strand Rememberers: selling pre-Fracture cartographic materials to Kowloon
and Kiess
